7. ABSOLUTE PROHIBITION OF MILITARY AND WEAPONS USE

  a) Fundamental Principle:
     The use of this Software — in whole or in part, in original or modified
     form — for the development, design, testing, deployment, operation,
     maintenance, or support of weapons, weapon systems, or weapon-like
     devices is strictly and absolutely prohibited. This prohibition is
     unconditional and admits no exceptions, regardless of intent, context,
     or authorization by any governmental, military, or other entity.

  b) Prohibited Applications Include, Without Limitation:
     (i)   Weapons of any kind, including but not limited to firearms,
           artillery, missiles, rockets, bombs, explosives, directed-energy
           weapons, chemical weapons, biological weapons, and nuclear weapons;

     (ii)  Weapon-like drones and unmanned systems, including but not limited
           to aerial drones (UAVs), ground-based unmanned vehicles (UGVs),
           naval unmanned vehicles (UNVs), and autonomous or semi-autonomous
           robotic platforms designed, equipped, or intended to carry, deploy,
           aim, fire, or otherwise utilize weapons or weapon-like mechanisms;

     (iii) Weapon targeting systems, fire control systems, guidance systems,
           trigger mechanisms, detonation systems, or any component thereof;

     (iv)  Military command and control systems, weapons navigation systems,
           or any system whose primary or secondary purpose is the direction,
           coordination, or execution of lethal force;

     (v)   Surveillance or reconnaissance systems that are integrated with,
           feed data to, or are operated in conjunction with weapons systems
           or weapon-like drones;

     (vi)  Any device, system, or mechanism that is functionally equivalent
           to a weapon or weapon-like drone, regardless of its designation,
           classification, or stated purpose;

     (vii) Any research, development, testing, or simulation activity whose
           direct purpose is to advance, improve, or enable any of the above.

  c) Dual-Use Prohibition:
     This prohibition applies equally to dual-use technologies — systems that
     may have legitimate civilian or peaceful applications but are also used,
     integrated with, or repurposed for weapons or weapon-like drones. The
     existence of a non-military use case does not exempt a project from this
     prohibition if any aspect of the project involves weapons or weapon-like
     drones as described in Section 7(b).

  d) No Authorization by Proxy:
     No government, military organization, defense contractor, law enforcement
     agency, or any other entity may authorize, permit, or override this
     prohibition. This restriction is inherent to the License and cannot be
     waived by any party other than the Author — and the Author expressly
     declares that no such waiver shall ever be granted for the uses described
     in this Section.

  e) Consequences of Violation:
     Any use of this Software in violation of this Section constitutes a
     material breach and shall result in:

     (i)   Immediate and automatic termination of all rights granted under
           this License;

     (ii)  An obligation to pay a penalty of EUR 10,000,000 (ten million
           Euros) per violation, per weapon system or weapon-like drone
           deployed, tested, or developed using this Software;

     (iii) An obligation to immediately cease all use of this Software,
           remove it from all systems, and destroy all copies in their
           possession or control;

     (iv)  Full liability for all damages, including but not limited to
           harm caused by weapons or weapon-like drones developed, operated,
           or supported using this Software, as well as all legal costs,
           investigative costs, and consequential damages.

  f) Affirmative Duty:
     Any entity or individual using this Software in a context where weapons
     or weapon-like drones are developed, tested, or operated in any capacity
     within the same organization, project, or facility has an affirmative
     duty to ensure strict and verifiable separation between any use of this
     Software and any weapons-related activity. Mere assertion of separation
     is insufficient — the Licensee must maintain auditable evidence of
     complete isolation.

